1.10	Brodno	Brodno	Brodno is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Środa Śląska, within Środa Śląska County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately 9 kilometres (6 mi) north of Środa Śląska and 34 km (21 mi) west of the regional capital Wrocław.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/06/Poland_location_map.svg/250px-Poland_location_map.svg.png
